13/06/2007
DAMASCUS, Syria -- Greek Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis called for the EU to become more involved in the Middle East peace process, during a visit to Syria on Tuesday (June 12th) as part of a tour of the region. 
Her meeting with Syrian President Bashar al-Assad focused on the situation in the region, particularly issues related to Lebanon, the Palestinian territories and Iraq. 
Greece wants to encourage moderation, dialogue and co-operation, Bakoyannis said. 
Later Tuesday, she headed for Amman. 
(AFP - 13/06/07; ANA-MPA, ERT, Kathimerini - 12/06/07)
